     "id": "e6eac63e-a461-472b-8aba-97deb9fab499"
    }
   ],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(* Closed-form pattern.\n\nWriting n=(u-θ)/h and ζ=κ2/κ1, the explicit q_M(u) computed above (for each λ,M) match,\nup to overall normalization, the hypergeometric (Krawtchouk-type) polynomial\n\n  q_M(u) = ₂F₁(-M, -(u-θ)/h ; -λ ; 1-κ2/κ1)\n         = Sum_{k=0}^{M} Pochhammer[-M,k] Pochhammer[-(u-θ)/h,k] / (Pochhammer[-λ,k] k!) (1-κ2/κ1)^k\n\nVerified below by substituting this closed form DIRECTLY into the original\n(unstripped) TQ relation for λ=1,...,4 and all M=0,...,λ. *)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "ClearAll[qClosed];\nqClosed[λ_,M_][u_] := Sum[Pochhammer[-M,k] Pochhammer[-(u-θ)/h,k]/(Pochhammer[-λ,k] k!) (1-κ2/κ1)^k, {k,0,M}];\n\ntqEqClosed[λ_,M_][u_] := κ1 Qθ[u - λ h] qClosed[λ,M][u+h] - tEigenvalue[λ,M][u] qClosed[λ,M][u] + κ2 Qθ[u] qClosed[λ,M][u-h] // Simplify;\nTable[tqEqClosed[λ,M][u], {λ,1,4},{M,0,λ}] // Flatten // Union",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
       "data": "<div class=\"wl-output-block\"><div class=\"wl-output-header\" style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;width:100%;min-height:22px;\" data-session-epoch=\"638911\" data-output-id=\"10\" data-out-n=\"55\" data-sub-idx=\"3\" data-output-format=\"WLLatex\" data-output-is-graphics=\"0\" data-cell-idx=\"23\" data-sub-start=\"4\" data-sub-end=\"4\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;color:#888;margin-right:8px;\">Out[55]=</span></div><div class=\"wl-output-content\"><div class=\"vscode-wolfram-wllatex-prerendered wl-lb-pending\" data-lb-id=\"lb-mrknf99b-xpywj6m\" data-page-width-em=\"10\" data-latex-b64=\"XGxlZnRcezBccmlnaHRcfQ==\" style=\"opacity:0.65;transition:opacity 0.35s\"><div class=\"wl-lb-content\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">{</span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">}</span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div></div></div>",
       "mime": "x-application/wolfram-language-html"
      },
      {
       "data": "Out[55]= \\left\\{0\\right\\}",
       "mime": "text/plain"
      }
     ],
     "id": "02063f2e-9255-42a5-b7c6-5c38cdf16474"
    }
   ],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(* Baxter TQ-equation solver, part 3: eigenvector Ψ[λ,M] of t[λ][1,1][u].\n\nKey observation: t[λ][1,1][u] = u(κ1+κ2) Id + (u-independent piece), i.e. it is u times the\nidentity plus a fixed matrix - so its EIGENVECTORS do not depend on u at all (only the\neigenvalues shift linearly with u). We therefore diagonalize t[λ][1,1][u] once (at the\nconvenient point u->0, after applying twistSubst χ1,χ2->κ1,κ2), and pick out the\neigenvector whose eigenvalue matches tEigenvalue[λ,M][0]. Normalization convention:\nwhatever Eigensystem returns (no further rescaling). *)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "ClearAll[Ψ];\nΨ[λ_,M_] := Module[{tm,es,vals,vecs,pos,raw,overlap},\n   tm = t[λ][1,1][u] /. twistSubst /. u -> 0;\n   es = Eigensystem[tm];\n   vals = es[[1]];\n   vecs = es[[2]];\n   pos = First @ FirstPosition[vals, v_ /; Simplify[v - (tEigenvalue[λ,M][u] /. u -> 0)] === 0];\n   raw = vecs[[pos]];\n   (* normalize so that x[λ][{0}].Ψ[λ,M] == 1; overlap is proportional to the bottom\n      component of raw (x[λ][{0}] is a KroneckerDelta pick-out of the last entry) *)\n   overlap = Simplify[First[x[λ][{0}].raw]];\n   If[overlap === 0, Message[Ψ::zeroOverlap,λ,M]; $Failed, raw/overlap]\n];\nΨ::zeroOverlap = \"Raw eigenvector overlap with x[`1`][{0}] vanishes for λ=`1`, M=`2` - cannot normalize.\";",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(* Sanity check: Ψ[λ,M] must satisfy t[λ][1,1][u].Ψ[λ,M] == tEigenvalue[λ,M][u] Ψ[λ,M]\nidentically in u (not just at u=0), for every λ=2,3 and every valid M=0,...,λ. *)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "Table[\n  Simplify[(t[λ][1,1][u]/.twistSubst).Ψ[λ,M] - tEigenvalue[λ,M][u] Ψ[λ,M]],\n{λ,2,3},{M,0,λ}] // Flatten // Union",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
       "data": "<div class=\"wl-output-block\"><div class=\"wl-output-header\" style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;width:100%;min-height:22px;\" data-session-epoch=\"638911\" data-output-id=\"12\" data-out-n=\"59\" data-sub-idx=\"0\" data-output-format=\"WLLatex\" data-output-is-graphics=\"0\" data-cell-idx=\"27\" data-sub-start=\"0\" data-sub-end=\"2\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;color:#888;margin-right:8px;\">Out[59]=</span></div><div class=\"wl-output-content\"><div class=\"vscode-wolfram-wllatex-prerendered wl-lb-pending\" data-lb-id=\"lb-mrknz4mo-6t2brjc\" data-page-width-em=\"29\" data-latex-b64=\"XGxlZnRcezBccmlnaHRcfQ==\" style=\"opacity:0.65;transition:opacity 0.35s\"><div class=\"wl-lb-content\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">{</span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">}</span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div></div></div>",
       "mime": "x-application/wolfram-language-html"
      },
      {
       "data": "Out[59]= \\left\\{0\\right\\}",
       "mime": "text/plain"
      }
     ],
     "id": "eb0c9ba9-e690-4e56-bd31-32cc245b0b11"
    }
   ],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(* Normalization check: x[λ][{0}].Ψ[λ,M] == 1 identically, for λ=1,...,4, all valid M. *)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "Table[\n  Simplify[First[x[λ][{0}].Ψ[λ,M]] - 1],\n{λ,1,4},{M,0,λ}] // Flatten // Union",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
       "data": "<div class=\"wl-output-block\"><div class=\"wl-output-header\" style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;width:100%;min-height:22px;\" data-session-epoch=\"638911\" data-output-id=\"13\" data-out-n=\"60\" data-sub-idx=\"0\" data-output-format=\"WLLatex\" data-output-is-graphics=\"0\" data-cell-idx=\"29\" data-sub-start=\"0\" data-sub-end=\"2\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;color:#888;margin-right:8px;\">Out[60]=</span></div><div class=\"wl-output-content\"><div class=\"vscode-wolfram-wllatex-prerendered wl-lb-pending\" data-lb-id=\"lb-mrknz80b-9p3g6vu\" data-page-width-em=\"29\" data-latex-b64=\"XGxlZnRcezBccmlnaHRcfQ==\" style=\"opacity:0.65;transition:opacity 0.35s\"><div class=\"wl-lb-content\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">{</span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">}</span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div></div></div>",
       "mime": "x-application/wolfram-language-html"
      },
      {
       "data": "Out[60]= \\left\\{0\\right\\}",
       "mime": "text/plain"
      }
     ],
     "id": "55b89be1-7612-469b-ab38-c3f67d2ae1f0"
    }
   ],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(* SoV wavefunction reconstruction check.\n\nClaim: x[λ][{s}].Ψ[λ,M] == Q_M(θ+hs)/Q_M(θ), s=0,...,λ, where Q_M(u)=κ1^(u/h) qSolution[λ,M][u]\nis the FULL Q-function (polynomial part times the κ1^(u/h) prefactor), exactly as assembled\nin fullVerify of cell 21 (Qf[v_]:=κ1^(v/h) qSolution[λ,M][v]). s=0 is trivial by construction\n(both sides ==1, since x[λ][{0}].Ψ[λ,M]==1 by cell 30's normalization and Q_M(θ)/Q_M(θ)==1).\nChecked below for λ=1,...,4, all valid M=0,...,λ, s=0,...,λ. *)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "ClearAll[QFull];\nQFull[λ_,M_][v_] := κ1^(v/h) qSolution[λ,M][v];\n\nreconstructionCheck = Table[\n   Simplify[First[x[λ][{s}].Ψ[λ,M]] - QFull[λ,M][θ+h s]/QFull[λ,M][θ]],\n{λ,1,4},{M,0,λ},{s,0,λ}] // Flatten // Union",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
       "data": "<div class=\"wl-output-block\"><div class=\"wl-output-header\" style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;width:100%;min-height:22px;\" data-session-epoch=\"638911\" data-output-id=\"14\" data-out-n=\"63\" data-sub-idx=\"2\" data-output-format=\"WLLatex\" data-output-is-graphics=\"0\" data-cell-idx=\"31\" data-sub-start=\"3\" data-sub-end=\"5\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;color:#888;margin-right:8px;\">Out[63]=</span></div><div class=\"wl-output-content\"><div class=\"vscode-wolfram-wllatex-prerendered wl-lb-pending\" data-lb-id=\"lb-mrko3a3d-d99g7fy\" data-page-width-em=\"29\" data-latex-b64=\"XGxlZnRcezBccmlnaHRcfQ==\" style=\"opacity:0.65;transition:opacity 0.35s\"><div class=\"wl-lb-content\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">{</span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">}</span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div></div></div>",
       "mime": "x-application/wolfram-language-html"
      },
      {
       "data": "Out[63]= \\left\\{0\\right\\}",
       "mime": "text/plain"
      }
     ],
     "id": "b2ac9f76-b680-4238-8922-5e9f752ed948"
    }
   ],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(* control: same check but with the κ1^(u/h) prefactor OMITTED (bare polynomial ratio\nqSolution[λ,M][θ+hs]/qSolution[λ,M][θ] only) - confirms the prefactor is NOT redundant,\ni.e. it does not cancel in the ratio and is genuinely required for the identity to hold *)\nTable[\n   Simplify[First[x[λ][{s}].Ψ[λ,M]] - qSolution[λ,M][θ+h s]/qSolution[λ,M][θ]],\n{λ,1,4},{M,1,λ},{s,1,λ}] // Flatten // Union // Length",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
       "data": "<div class=\"wl-output-block\"><div class=\"wl-output-header\" style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;width:100%;min-height:22px;\" data-session-epoch=\"638911\" data-output-id=\"15\" data-out-n=\"64\" data-sub-idx=\"1\" data-output-format=\"WLLatex\" data-output-is-graphics=\"0\" data-cell-idx=\"32\" data-sub-start=\"3\" data-sub-end=\"5\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;color:#888;margin-right:8px;\">Out[64]=</span></div><div class=\"wl-output-content\"><div class=\"vscode-wolfram-wllatex-prerendered wl-lb-pending\" data-lb-id=\"lb-mrko3aq4-m5y3fj5\" data-page-width-em=\"29\" data-latex-b64=\"MjM=\" style=\"opacity:0.65;transition:opacity 0.35s\"><div class=\"wl-lb-content\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">23</span></span></span></span></span></div></div></div></div>",
       "mime": "x-application/wolfram-language-html"
      },
      {
       "data": "Out[64]= 23",
       "mime": "text/plain"
      }
     ],
     "id": "aa86d618-8662-4103-b3ae-79e6628e249a"
    }
   ],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(* Result: reconstructionCheck == {0} identically for all λ=1,...,4, M=0,...,λ, s=0,...,λ -\nthe SoV reconstruction identity x[λ][{s}].Ψ[λ,M] == Q_M(θ+hs)/Q_M(θ) holds EXACTLY, with no\nextra normalization constant, sign, or M/λ-dependent factor needed. The control check (bare\npolynomial qSolution only, prefactor dropped) gives a nonzero, κ1/κ2-dependent set of residuals\n- so the κ1^(u/h) prefactor in Q_M(u) is essential and does NOT cancel in the ratio\n(only the M/λ-independent overall normalization of qSolution, and κ1^(θ/h), drop out). *)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(* SoV measure: normalized contour-integral functional.\n\nDefine μ[λ](u) = Product[1/(u - θ - h(k-1)), {k,1,λ+1}] (λ+1 simple poles at u = θ, θ+h, ..., θ+hλ,\nmatching the FULL SoV covector basis x[λ][{s}], s=0,...,λ), and the contour functional\n⟨f⟩ = 2πi Σ_{k=1}^{λ+1} Residue[μ[λ](u) f(u), u=θ+h(k-1)] (contour just encircling the λ+1\npoles, f assumed entire).\n\nThe residue at pole j (u=θ+h(j-1)) is f(θ+h(j-1)) (-1)^{λ+1-j} / [h^λ (j-1)! (λ+1-j)!], so the\nf(θ) term (j=1) has coefficient 2πi (-1)^λ / [h^λ λ!]. Normalizing by\n\n  normConst[λ] = (-1)^λ h^λ λ! / (2πi)\n\nso that the f(θ) coefficient is exactly 1, the residue sum collapses (verified below, both\nsymbolically for generic f and on monomials u^n) to the alternating-binomial finite-difference form\n\n  ⟨f⟩_normalized = Sum[(-1)^i Binomial[λ,i] f(θ+h i), {i,0,λ}]\n\ni.e. exactly (-1)^λ times the λ-th forward finite difference of f at θ with step h. *)",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(* measure with λ+1 simple poles at u = θ+h(k-1), k=1,...,λ+1 - matches the FULL SoV\ncovector basis x[λ][{s}], s=0,...,λ (λ+1 basis states total) *)\nClearAll[μ];\nμ[λ_][u_] := Product[1/(u - θ - h(k-1)), {k, 1, λ+1}];",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(* raw contour functional = 2πi * sum of residues, computed directly via Residue *)\nClearAll[residueSum];\nresidueSum[λ_][f_] := 2 Pi I Sum[Residue[μ[λ][u] f[u], {u, θ + h(k-1)}], {k, 1, λ+1}];\nTable[residueSum[λ][f], {λ,1,4}]",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
