  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(* Result: normConst[λ] = (-1)^λ h^λ λ! / (2πi) exactly cancels the f(θ)-term\ncoefficient of the raw residue sum, and the normalized functional SoVMeasure[λ][f] =\nSum[(-1)^i Binomial[λ,i] f(θ+h i), {i,0,λ}] reproduces the normalized contour integral\nidentically for λ=1,...,6 (symbolic f) and on the monomial basis f(u)=u^n, n=0,...,λ, for\nλ=1,...,4 (all differences {0}). So ⟨f⟩_normalized = f(θ) - λ f(θ+h) + Binomial[λ,2] f(θ+2h)\n- ... + (-1)^λ f(θ+hλ), matching the anticipated alternating finite-difference pattern over\nthe FULL (λ+1)-point SoV basis. *)",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(* Generic-Q algebraic check: apply SoVMeasure to u |-> w^(u/h) Q(u) for an ABSTRACT\nfunction Q (not assumed to solve the TQ equation) and a free formal parameter w (new\nsymbol, unused elsewhere in this notebook). Since SoVMeasure[λ][f] now samples f at the\nλ+1 points θ, θ+h, ..., θ+hλ, and w^((θ+h i)/h) = w^(θ/h) w^i splits multiplicatively,\ndividing by Q(θ) w^(θ/h) should strip off the common w^(θ/h) Q(θ) factor and leave a pure\nsum over s=0,...,λ of the wavefunction ratios Q(θ+hs)/Q(θ) weighted by\nc_s(w,λ) = (-1)^s Binomial[λ,s] w^s - i.e. the same binomial coefficients that appear in\nSoVMeasure itself, now dressed with w^s. Checked below symbolically for λ=1,...,4 with Q\nleft completely undefined (opaque function head). *)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "ClearAll[R,c,claimedR];\nR[λ_] := SoVMeasure[λ][Function[u, w^(u/h) Q[u]]] / (Q[θ] w^(θ/h));\n(* claimed closed-form coefficients c_s(w,λ) and the resulting sum over SoV wavefunction values *)\nc[s_,λ_] := (-1)^s Binomial[λ,s] w^s;\nclaimedR[λ_] := Sum[c[s,λ] (Q[θ+h s]/Q[θ]), {s,0,λ}];\nR[1]",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
       "data": "<div class=\"wl-output-block\"><div class=\"wl-output-header\" style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;width:100%;min-height:22px;\" data-session-epoch=\"638911\" data-output-id=\"27\" data-out-n=\"106\" data-sub-idx=\"5\" data-output-format=\"WLLatex\" data-output-is-graphics=\"0\" data-cell-idx=\"42\" data-sub-start=\"5\" data-sub-end=\"5\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;color:#888;margin-right:8px;\">Out[106]=</span></div><div class=\"wl-output-content\"><div class=\"vscode-wolfram-wllatex-prerendered wl-lb-pending\" data-lb-id=\"lb-mrkoxm41-87456bi\" data-page-width-em=\"12\" data-latex-b64=\"XGZyYWN7d157LVxmcmFje1x0aGV0YSB9e2h9fVwsXGxlZnQoUVxsZWZ0KFx0aGV0YSBccmlnaHQpXCx3XntcZnJhY3tcdGhldGEgfXtofX0tUVxsZWZ0KGgrXHRoZXRhIFxyaWdodClcLHdee1xmcmFje2grXHRoZXRhIH17aH19XHJpZ2h0KX17UVxsZWZ0KFx0aGV0YSBccmlnaHQpfQ==\" style=\"opacity:0.65;transition:opacity 0.35s\"><div class=\"wl-lb-content\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:3.126em;vertical-align:-0.936em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mopen nulldelimiter\"></span><span class=\"mfrac\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:2.19em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.464em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">θ</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">)</span></span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.38em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3.15em;\"></span><span class=\"frac-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-4.19em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3.15em;\"