mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">h</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">θ</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">)</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02691em;\">w</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.979em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.363em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mopen nulldelimiter sizing reset-size3 size6\"></span><span class=\"mfrac\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.88em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.656em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size3 size1 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">h</span></span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.2255em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"frac-line mtight\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.049em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.384em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size3 size1 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">h</span><span class=\"mbin mtight\">+</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">θ</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.344em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose nulldelimiter sizing reset-size3 size6\"></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size2\">)</span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.936em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose nulldelimiter\"></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div></div></div>",
       "mime": "x-application/wolfram-language-html"
      },
      {
       "data": "Out[106]= \\frac{w^{-\\frac{\\theta }{h}}\\,\\left(Q\\left(\\theta \\right)\\,w^{\\frac{\\theta }{h}}-Q\\left(h+\\theta \\right)\\,w^{\\frac{h+\\theta }{h}}\\right)}{Q\\left(\\theta \\right)}",
       "mime": "text/plain"
      }
     ],
     "id": "9ed2104f-4284-4b72-bd76-deb5f43f7593"
    }
   ],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(* Verification: R[λ] - claimedR[λ] must vanish identically for λ=1,...,4, with Q an\nopaque symbolic function (Q[u_] left undefined) and w a free formal parameter. *)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "genericCheck = Table[Simplify[R[λ] - claimedR[λ]], {λ,1,4}]",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
       "data": "<div class=\"wl-output-block\"><div class=\"wl-output-header\" style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;width:100%;min-height:22px;\" data-session-epoch=\"638911\" data-output-id=\"28\" data-out-n=\"107\" data-sub-idx=\"0\" data-output-format=\"WLLatex\" data-output-is-graphics=\"0\" data-cell-idx=\"44\" data-sub-start=\"0\" data-sub-end=\"0\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;color:#888;margin-right:8px;\">Out[107]=</span></div><div class=\"wl-output-content\"><div class=\"vscode-wolfram-wllatex-prerendered wl-lb-pending\" data-lb-id=\"lb-mrkoxm9c-psb13z5\" data-page-width-em=\"12\" data-latex-b64=\"XGxlZnRcezAsMCwwLDBccmlnaHRcfQ==\" style=\"opacity:0.65;transition:opacity 0.35s\"><div class=\"wl-lb-content\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">{</span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">}</span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div></div></div>",
       "mime": "x-application/wolfram-language-html"
      },
      {
       "data": "Out[107]= \\left\\{0,0,0,0\\right\\}",
       "mime": "text/plain"
      }
     ],
     "id": "3dd4439c-5e72-4571-b7f9-64c30e89ea27"
    }
   ],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(* Result: genericCheck == {0,0,0,0} - the identity\n\n  R[λ] = <w^(u/h) Q(u)> / (Q(θ) w^(θ/h)) = Sum[(-1)^s Binomial[λ,s] w^s Q[θ+h s]/Q[θ], {s,0,λ}]\n\nholds EXACTLY for λ=1,...,4 with Q completely abstract (no TQ-equation input used) and w a\nfree parameter. This is pure algebra: SoVMeasure[λ] samples f at θ,θ+h,...,θ+hλ, and\nw^((θ+hs)/h) = w^(θ/h) w^s factors out, leaving the same alternating binomial coefficients\nas SoVMeasure itself, now dressed with w^s. Final closed-form coefficients:\n\n  c_s(w,λ) = (-1)^s Binomial[λ,s] w^s ,  s = 0,...,λ\n\nso R[λ] = Sum[c_s(w,λ) Q(θ+hs)/Q(θ), {s,0,λ}], i.e. w^s just reweights the SoV wavefunction\nreconstruction coefficients from cell 32's identity x[λ][{s}].Ψ[λ,M] == Q_M(θ+hs)/Q_M(θ). *)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(* Identifying the covector state realizing R[λ] via the genuine SoV pairing.\n\nCombining Q[θ+hs]/Q[θ] == x[λ][{s}].Ψ[λ,M] (cells 25-34, valid for Q=Q_M a genuine\nTQ-solution) with the cell 42-46 result (linear in Q, hence linear in the covector\nargument by the same coefficients), gives\n\n  R[λ] (with Q -> Q_M) == φ[λ,w].Ψ[λ,M]\n\nwhere φ[λ,w] := Sum[(-1)^s Binomial[λ,s] w^s x[λ][{s}], {s,0,λ}] is a specific finite\nlinear combination of the FULL SoV covector basis x[λ][{0}],...,x[λ][{λ}] (all λ+1 basis\nstates - unlike the earlier buggy λ-pole version, which spuriously dropped the top state\ns=λ). Checked below directly against a genuine TQ solution Q_M (via QFull[λ,M] from\ncell 32), not just an abstract Q, for λ=1,...,4 and all valid M. *)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "ClearAll[φ];\nφ[λ_,w_] := Sum[(-1)^s Binomial[λ,s] w^s x[λ][{s}], {s,0,λ}];\n\nphiCheck = Table[\n   Simplify[First[φ[λ,w].Ψ[λ,M]] - SoVMeasure[λ][Function[u, w^(u/h) QFull[λ,M][u]]]/(QFull[λ,M][θ] w^(θ/h))],\n{λ,1,4},{M,0,λ}] // Flatten // Union",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
       "data": "<div class=\"wl-output-block\"><div class=\"wl-output-header\" style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;width:100%;min-height:22px;\" data-session-epoch=\"638911\" data-output-id=\"29\" data-out-n=\"110\" data-sub-idx=\"2\" data-output-format=\"WLLatex\" data-output-is-graphics=\"0\" data-cell-idx=\"47\" data-sub-start=\"3\" data-sub-end=\"5\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;color:#888;margin-right:8px;\">Out[110]=</span></div><div class=\"wl-output-content\"><div class=\"vscode-wolfram-wllatex-prerendered wl-lb-pending\" data-lb-id=\"lb-mrkoxmmq-52cq2op\" data-page-width-em=\"12\" data-latex-b64=\"XGxlZnRcezBccmlnaHRcfQ==\" style=\"opacity:0.65;transition:opacity 0.35s\"><div class=\"wl-lb-content\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">{</span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">}</span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div></div></div>",
       "mime": "x-application/wolfram-language-html"
      },
      {
       "data": "Out[110]= \\left\\{0\\right\\}",
       "mime": "text/plain"
      }
     ],
     "id": "dda06cdd-878d-4318-869b-2b32d6b712a6"
    }
   ],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(* Result: phiCheck == {0} identically for λ=1,...,4, all valid M=0,...,λ - the covector\nφ[λ,w] genuinely reproduces the SoV-measure ratio when paired with the true eigenvector\nΨ[λ,M], not just algebraically with an abstract Q. This confirms\n\n  φ[λ,w].Ψ[λ,M] == SoVMeasure[λ][w^(u/h) Q_M[u]] / (Q_M[θ] w^(θ/h))\n\nas an identity among genuine SoV data (FULL basis covectors x[λ][{s}], s=0,...,λ,\neigenvector Ψ[λ,M], TQ-solution Q_M via QFull[λ,M]). *)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(* State identification: the covector\n\n  <φ_w| := Sum[(-1)^s Binomial[λ,s] w^s <x_s|, {s,0,λ}]\n\ni.e. φ[λ,w] = Sum[(-1)^s Binomial[λ,s] w^s x[λ][{s}], {s,0,λ}], is the state satisfying\n\n  <φ_w|Ψ[λ,M]> == <w^(u/h) Q_M(u)> / (Q_M(θ) w^(θ/h))\n\nwhere <...> denotes the SoV-measure functional SoVMeasure[λ][...] of cells 35-41 (now built\nfrom λ+1 poles, matching the full (λ+1)-dimensional SoV basis), Ψ[λ,M] is the eigenvector of\ncell 26, and Q_M is the genuine TQ-equation solution of cells 20-24. *)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(* Pinning down the state identification: compare φ[λ,w] (cells 47-50) directly against\nx[λ][{0}].MatrixExp[Ee[λ][i,j] ζ] (the global-rotation covector of cells 12-14) for the\ncandidate generator (i,j)=(2,1) [natural guess from matching Binomial[λ,s]ζ^s vs\n(-1)^s Binomial[λ,s]w^s] and the alternative (i,j)=(1,2), each against several candidate\nrelations ζ(w). λ=1,...,4 throughout. *)\nstateCheck = <|\n   \"(2,1), ζ=-w\"   -> (Table[φ[λ,w] - (x[λ][{0}].MatrixExp[Ee[λ][2,1] ζ] /. ζ -> -w), {λ,1,4}] // Simplify // Flatten // Union),\n   \"(2,1), ζ=w\"    -> (Table[φ[λ,w] - (x[λ][{0}].MatrixExp[Ee[λ][2,1] ζ] /. ζ -> w), {λ,1,4}] // Simplify // Flatten // Union),\n   \"(2,1), ζ=1/w\"  -> (Table[φ[λ,w] - (x[λ][{0}].MatrixExp[Ee[λ][2,1] ζ] /. ζ -> 1/w), {λ,1,4}] // Simplify // Flatten // Union),\n   \"(2,1), ζ=-1/w\" -> (Table[φ[λ,w] - (x[λ][{0}].MatrixExp[Ee[λ][2,1] ζ] /. ζ -> -1/w), {λ,1,4}] // Simplify // Flatten // Union),\n   \"(1,2), ζ=-w\"   -> (Table[φ[λ,w] - (x[λ][{0}].MatrixExp[Ee[λ][1,2] ζ] /. ζ -> -w), {λ,1,4}] // Simplify // Flatten // Union),\n   \"(1,2), ζ=w\"    -> (Table[φ[λ,w] - (x[λ][{0}].MatrixExp[Ee[λ][1,2] ζ] /. ζ -> w), {λ,1,4}] // Simplify // Flatten // Union),\n   \"(1,2), ζ=1/w\"  -> (Table[φ[λ,w] - (x[λ][{0}].MatrixExp[Ee[λ][1,2] ζ] /. ζ -> 1/w), {λ,1,4}] // Simplify // Flatten // Union),\n   \"(1,2), ζ=-1/w\" -> (Table[φ[λ,w] - (x[λ][{0}].MatrixExp[Ee[λ][1,2] ζ] /. ζ -> -1/w), {λ,1,4}] // Simplify // Flatten // Union)\n|>",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
