  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(* Result: of the 8 (generator, ζ-relation) combinations tested (all against φ[λ,w],\nλ=1,...,4), only\n\n  (i,j)=(2,1), ζ=-w\n\ngives an identically-zero residual - i.e.\n\n  φ[λ,w] == x[λ][{0}].MatrixExp[Ee[λ][2,1] ζ] /. ζ -> -w\n\nexactly, for all λ=1,...,4. This matches the naive expectation from cell 14\n(c[λ][s]=Binomial[λ,s]ζ^s) combined with φ's coefficients (-1)^s Binomial[λ,s]w^s: setting\nζ=-w turns Binomial[λ,s]ζ^s into (-1)^s Binomial[λ,s]w^s exactly.\n\nAll 7 other combinations tried - (2,1) with ζ=w,1/w,-1/w, and (1,2) with ζ=-w,w,1/w,-1/w -\nfail with nonzero, λ-and-w-dependent residuals (no accidental near-matches; the (1,2) cases\nall give the SAME nonvanishing residual regardless of the ζ(w) substitution, since\nx[λ][{0}].Ee[λ][1,2]==0 makes x[λ][{0}].MatrixExp[Ee[λ][1,2]ζ]==x[λ][{0}] independent of ζ).\n\nConfirmed state identification:\n\n  <φ_w| = <x_0| MatrixExp[ -w Ee[λ][2,1] ]\n\ni.e. φ[λ,w] is the SoV vacuum covector x[λ][{0}] globally rotated by the lowering generator\nEe[λ][2,1] with rotation parameter ζ=-w. *)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  }
 ],
